1
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:34,833
"Wooju Bakery"

2
00:00:41,083 --> 00:00:45,250
What do you call that thing we were just
on?

3
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:47,625
This?

4
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,708
I'm not sure what it's called either.

5
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:52,250
It's actually pretty amazing.

6
00:00:52,917 --> 00:00:54,875
Oh, you mean a swing?

7
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:55,792
A swing!

8
00:00:56,958 --> 00:00:58,458
Swings are so much fun.

9
00:00:59,917 --> 00:01:01,083
Oh!

10
00:01:01,417 --> 00:01:04,417
Your Highness, I'm sorry!

11
00:01:04,792 --> 00:01:06,083
Get up.

12
00:01:07,458 --> 00:01:09,250
I'm the reason Hachi got arrested.

13
00:01:09,375 --> 00:01:12,167
What do you mean he got caught because of
you?

14
00:01:12,292 --> 00:01:13,833
The police got him

15
00:01:13,958 --> 00:01:15,750
when I wasn't paying attention.

16
00:01:15,875 --> 00:01:17,333
Let's go check on him first.

17
00:01:17,792 --> 00:01:18,958
Thankfully…

18
00:01:19,083 --> 00:01:21,083
- Huh?
- He got away…

19
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,083
- He's here.
- Huh?

20
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:28,125
Why didn't you say so sooner? You scared
me to death!

21
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:29,167
Your Highness…

22
00:01:29,292 --> 00:01:31,375
Please don't send him to jail!

23
00:01:31,917 --> 00:01:34,083
Hachi! Hands up!

24
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:37,583
Hands down.

25
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:41,708
Hey! Are you a dog? Are you?

26
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:42,917
Why are you eating dog food?

27
00:01:43,042 --> 00:01:45,625
Because… I can't resist the smell of it.

28
00:01:46,083 --> 00:01:48,208
Ugh…

29
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:50,083
I'm speechless… Hey!

30
00:01:50,208 --> 00:01:52,625
If word gets out that I'm feeding my
bakery staff dog food,

31
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,125
that I'm some kind of sweatshop owner,

32
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:55,542
what am I supposed to do?

33
00:01:55,667 --> 00:01:58,375
- Huh?
- Aren't you already a sweatshop owner?

34
00:01:58,667 --> 00:02:01,042
Seriously… How am I a sweatshop owner?

35
00:02:01,167 --> 00:02:02,542
You haven't paid our wages, have you?

36
00:02:02,667 --> 00:02:06,417
Oh, really? I knew you'd say that.

37
00:02:06,542 --> 00:02:08,042
Look, read the contract!

38
00:02:08,167 --> 00:02:11,625
You signed it yourself!

39
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:14,833
It's not that I'm not paying you.

40
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:18,250
You guys caused trouble, and now you're
working off your debt!

41
00:02:18,375 --> 00:02:19,167
Hmph.

42
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:22,000
Tsk!

43
00:02:37,542 --> 00:02:39,208
Um… Senior?

44
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:39,917
Yeah?

45
00:02:40,042 --> 00:02:41,375
That Wooju Bakery over there.

46
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:44,167
What now? Are you going to talk about
aliens again?

47
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:46,417
No, no.

48
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,292
Is their bread… any good?

49
00:02:48,417 --> 00:02:49,333
Why?

50
00:02:49,458 --> 00:02:50,958
Did someone say it wasn't good?

51
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:52,917
No, no, that's not it.

52
00:02:53,792 --> 00:02:56,000
Among the staff there,

53
00:02:56,125 --> 00:03:00,333
is there anyone who carries around some
kind of weird gun?

54
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:01,750
A gun?

55
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:05,625
What kind of gun?

56
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:07,167
No, I just…

57
00:03:07,292 --> 00:03:10,458
I think I might have been hit by some
weird gun.

58
00:03:10,583 --> 00:03:14,250
Maybe I was, maybe I wasn't… was I?

59
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:16,708
Did you finish handling that complaint
from yesterday?

60
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:17,750
Yes…

61
00:03:17,875 --> 00:03:19,500
I have to go, I've got things to do.

62
00:03:20,292 --> 00:03:21,667
Good work.

63
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:25,875
It's suspicious no matter how I look at
it.

64
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:28,750
Ugh… But how am I supposed to prove it?

65
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,833
That jerk… Wooju Bakery…

66
00:03:30,958 --> 00:03:33,958
Mina… Dragon Palace Restaurant… Jirol…

67
00:03:34,167 --> 00:03:38,250
Wait, wasn't Jirol already suspicious
before the bakery even opened?

68
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:39,625
He looks so dim-witted.

69
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:41,792
Could he be hiding the fact that he's an
evil alien?

70
00:03:41,917 --> 00:03:42,950
Is he putting on an act?

71
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,167
I'm back!

72
00:03:45,292 --> 00:03:47,542
Come here for a second.

73
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:50,500
You were only delivering nearby, why did
it take you so long?

74
00:03:50,625 --> 00:03:51,625
- Ouch…
- Why are you so late?

75
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:53,208
I thought something happened to you!

76
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,875
No, how could I possibly get into trouble?

77
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,250
I'm the best delivery guy in this
neighborhood.

78
00:03:57,375 --> 00:03:58,167
Cut the crap.

79
00:03:58,292 --> 00:04:02,125
All you do is dance and mess around with
those kids all day.

80
00:04:02,250 --> 00:04:03,000
That's not it.

81
00:04:03,125 --> 00:04:05,292
I'm doing it for the future customers of
Dragon Palace.

82
00:04:05,417 --> 00:04:07,667
I'm helping to attract customers, right?

83
00:04:07,792 --> 00:04:11,083
Enough. I'll give you one more chance. If
you drag your feet again,

84
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:12,833
I'm firing you, you hear me?

85
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:14,125
Yes…

86
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:15,542
Can you come out for a second? I have
something to tell you.

87
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:18,042
Officer… I didn't do anything wrong.

88
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:21,292
No, boss, it's not like that… I…

89
00:04:21,417 --> 00:04:22,875
I came here because I know everything!

90
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,292
What exactly do you know? Seriously.

91
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:26,917
Aliens!

92
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:29,292
You're one, aren't you?

93
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:32,958
No, I…

94
00:04:33,083 --> 00:04:34,292
You really…

95
00:04:34,583 --> 00:04:35,625
What aliens?

96
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,542
What are you even talking about?

97
00:04:37,667 --> 00:04:39,125
I'm not one.

98
00:04:39,958 --> 00:04:41,292
I'm a person who even have an ID card, you
know.

99
00:04:41,417 --> 00:04:44,417
Then why did you kidnap the YouTuber Mina
last time?

100
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:47,500
That was…

101
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:50,250
Rather than a kidnapping, it was more
like…

102
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:52,250
If you tell me the truth,

103
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,375
I might go easy on you.

104
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,875
I'm really not an alien, okay?

105
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:02,542
Actually, the alien…

106
00:05:04,958 --> 00:05:07,292
is a guy named Chairman Lee.

107
00:05:11,292 --> 00:05:12,292
Chairman Lee?

108
00:05:12,417 --> 00:05:14,750
He's truly despicable!

109
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:18,000
Despicable?

110
00:05:20,167 --> 00:05:21,250
Despicable?

111
00:05:21,375 --> 00:05:22,583
Yeah! Exactly.

112
00:05:22,708 --> 00:05:26,125
He's the kind of guy who came here to
destroy the Earth, seriously.

113
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,500
But…

114
00:05:29,042 --> 00:05:32,917
You can't tell anyone I told you, okay?

115
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:37,000
Tell me more clearly, I can go easy on
you…

116
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:42,708
Wooju Bakery, no bias, no hype, just an
honest review.

117
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,000
If you go to Wooju Bakery,

118
00:05:44,125 --> 00:05:46,167
You really have to choose your bread
carefully…

119
00:05:46,292 --> 00:05:47,583
Damn it.

120
00:05:49,917 --> 00:05:52,958
I don't want to just stand by and watch
the shop turn into a mess.

121
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:58,958
The boss hasn't even woken up yet, and
we've already cleaned the whole shop.

122
00:06:00,792 --> 00:06:03,708
That's not what I'm talking about! I mean…

123
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:07,542
A bakery is supposed to smell like fresh,
delicious bread.

124
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:12,583
And there should be customers quietly
coming in to buy bread.

125
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:15,333
Right now, it's just noisy and chaotic,
isn't it?

126
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:19,292
But the customers love it…

127
00:06:19,417 --> 00:06:20,833
Quiet!

128
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:22,875
The boss is talking.

129
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:30,625
Get rid of all those questionable breads
and start over.

130
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:32,667
But…

131
00:06:33,083 --> 00:06:35,125
The bread you make…

132
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,542
What about it?

133
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:38,125
It's really bad.

134
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,208
This is the place, right?

135
00:06:43,417 --> 00:06:45,083
Please wait a moment…

136
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:48,875
Try them all.

137
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,625
- They look so delicious.
- Those ones too.

138
00:07:04,042 --> 00:07:07,000
Boss, look over here.

139
00:07:07,125 --> 00:07:09,667
Only the bread you made hasn't sold.

140
00:07:11,292 --> 00:07:12,125
So annoying.

141
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:13,750
This bakery, even the bread is weird.

142
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:16,917
The drinks are weird, the staff is weird,
everything is weird.

143
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,333
The customers are the weirdest ones!

144
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:32,667
Scream!

145
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:37,917
Air!

146
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:40,000
Shut your mouth.

147
00:08:13,417 --> 00:08:15,042
Why are you up so early?

148
00:08:16,375 --> 00:08:20,500
Hey! Stop making noise and go back to
sleep.

149
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:23,667
The boss's bread isn't popular, so I'll
make some.

150
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:25,542
I told you to go back to sleep.

151
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,750
I said go back to sleep, are you deaf?

152
00:09:13,917 --> 00:09:15,292
Hmm~

153
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:17,833
The bread smells really good.

154
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,167
Why are you making that face?

155
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:30,500
Or… did I do something wrong?

156
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:32,667
No.

157
00:09:33,542 --> 00:09:37,958
Are you mad because I didn't help?

158
00:09:38,875 --> 00:09:40,833
I said it's not like that.

159
00:09:51,458 --> 00:09:53,625
I said it's not like that, can't you
understand?

160
00:09:54,292 --> 00:09:57,792
Alright, stop it.

161
00:09:57,917 --> 00:09:59,292
It's not because of you.

162
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:03,500
Then what is it?

163
00:10:08,375 --> 00:10:11,125
The smell of the bread baking right now…
do you like it?

164
00:10:18,542 --> 00:10:19,875
Yeah.

165
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:25,792
When I was little,

166
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:29,750
I always loved the smell when my dad made
bread.

167
00:10:29,875 --> 00:10:33,833
I really want to smell that again.

168
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:40,125
But now, I can't sense anything…

169
00:11:22,042 --> 00:11:24,917
Wow~ the bread smells so good.

170
00:11:25,042 --> 00:11:26,333
Hyung.

171
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,208
Why are you here so early?

172
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:34,042
I thought I'd bring some of your bread to
share at the station.

173
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:36,125
After all, you just opened recently.

174
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:37,625
Yeah.

175
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,458
Our bread doesn't need promotion.

176
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:41,333
Because it sells too well.

177
00:11:41,792 --> 00:11:43,875
Except for the bread Wooju makes.

178
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:47,250
I specifically want to buy the bread Wooju
makes.

179
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:52,417
The ones that just went into the oven need
a while.

180
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,708
At least 10 minutes.

181
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:59,167
Hmm? This one… I can just buy this one.

182
00:11:59,292 --> 00:12:01,583
Not that one… that one…

183
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:02,875
That's from yesterday.

184
00:12:03,583 --> 00:12:05,667
It doesn't matter, I'll take this one.

185
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,958
Uh…

186
00:12:11,417 --> 00:12:12,583
Yuck!

187
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:15,625
This is terrible. You call this bread?

188
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,375
No.

189
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:22,917
Isn't it a bit harsh to say it's terrible
right to his face?

190
00:12:23,042 --> 00:12:26,708
A baker should know whether their bread is
good or not.

191
00:12:26,958 --> 00:12:28,208
Hey~

192
00:12:52,792 --> 00:12:56,458
Wooju, your sense of taste will come back.

193
00:12:56,875 --> 00:13:00,083
Didn't the doctor say it was only
temporary?

194
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:02,333
Opening this bakery… it's really pushing
it.

195
00:13:02,458 --> 00:13:03,833
Boss.

196
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,167
Hmm?

197
00:13:07,542 --> 00:13:09,458
Boss, don't worry.

198
00:13:13,208 --> 00:13:14,625
You've got me.

199
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:15,958
What did you say?

200
00:13:17,208 --> 00:13:18,417
I'll teach you.

201
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:22,708
How to bake bread!

202
00:13:24,375 --> 00:13:25,875
The best bread in the world.

203
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:32,625
The best bread in the entire world?

204
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:35,833
What are you talking about, you fraud?

205
00:13:35,958 --> 00:13:38,500
Why would I want to learn

206
00:13:39,333 --> 00:13:40,750
how to make your weird bread?

207
00:13:44,292 --> 00:13:45,792
Hey?

208
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:50,125
Get out.

209
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:05,875
Hey.

210
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:09,542
Did you go to culinary school too?

211
00:14:09,667 --> 00:14:11,292
What makes you say that?

212
00:14:11,417 --> 00:14:15,167
Your technique… it's not bad.

213
00:14:15,292 --> 00:14:18,083
Do you want to give it a try?

214
00:14:25,667 --> 00:14:27,208
How do I do it?

215
00:14:44,042 --> 00:14:45,625
Take it slow.

216
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:04,292
How's that? Doesn't it feel smoother?

217
00:15:04,417 --> 00:15:08,875
I've never seen anyone bake bread like
that before.

218
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,167
Never?

219
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,667
I doubt that.

220
00:15:14,792 --> 00:15:16,000
I don't remember clearly…

221
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:20,958
But I think my dad used to bake bread just
like this.

222
00:15:22,875 --> 00:15:24,625
Think of your father.

223
00:15:26,417 --> 00:15:29,542
Imagine he's watching you right now.

224
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:32,000
Yeah.

225
00:15:38,042 --> 00:15:39,667
Now, it's time for a taste test.

226
00:15:39,792 --> 00:15:41,292
Want to try it?

227
00:15:43,458 --> 00:15:44,458
Sigh.

228
00:15:44,583 --> 00:15:46,042
Raon…

229
00:15:46,167 --> 00:15:47,625
Yeah?

230
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:55,208
Do you think I can really…

231
00:15:55,583 --> 00:15:58,292
Do you think I'll ever be able to taste
again?

232
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:05,500
Yeah.

233
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:09,292
That's good.

234
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:01,042
Well?

235
00:17:03,292 --> 00:17:05,167
Can you taste anything?

236
00:20:33,917 --> 00:20:35,583
Stop it.

237
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:37,792
Why not?

238
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:45,708
Chairman Lee, about Mr. Kim from the
salvage shop…

239
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:47,542
I can't shake this uneasy feeling.

240
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:50,250
Are you sure it's okay to just let him go?

241
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:53,292
That guy is a highly skilled engineer.

242
00:20:53,417 --> 00:20:56,542
They don't have a ship or any
communication gear anyway.

243
00:20:56,667 --> 00:21:00,958
If they want to go home, they'll have to
do exactly as we say.

244
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:03,083
Chairman Lee.

245
00:21:03,208 --> 00:21:04,333
How have you been?

246
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:06,458
Those people who crash-landed recently…

247
00:21:06,583 --> 00:21:08,000
They seem to be high-ranking officials.

248
00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:08,542
This…

249
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:09,875
The news from off-world is blowing up.

250
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,417
What? Tell me exactly who they are.

251
00:21:12,542 --> 00:21:15,500
They keep demanding the location of the
ship.

252
00:21:15,625 --> 00:21:19,333
But they won't reveal their identities or
where they're from.

253
00:21:20,583 --> 00:21:23,042
Find out where they are right now.

254
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,375
And bring them to me immediately.

255
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,375
Understood.

256
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,917
If we keep this up, won't it cause trouble
later?

257
00:21:29,042 --> 00:21:30,417
It doesn't matter.

258
00:21:31,708 --> 00:21:34,042
We just need to catch them before that
happens.

259
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:36,625
Understood.
